    "description": "Released: 1994\nGenre: House, Tribal House, Electronic\nLength: 48:23 (approx.)\nLabel: Strictly Rhythm Records\nProducer: Armand Van Helden\n\nThe Armand Van Helden EP is a 1994 release by New York City DJ/producer Armand Van Helden for Strictly Rhythm Records. Produced and mixed for Ya Muthas House Productions, its tribal house tracks would prove foundational for the future star. The opening track, \"Witch Doktor,\" became a classic of the era and, along with the other tracks, helped define the \"New York Tribal\" sound. The EP features five original tracks, plus two remixes of \"Witch Doktor,\" showcasing the producer's raw, beat-driven style during his early career.",
