    "description": "Released: October 26, 1999\nRecorded: Late 1999\nStudio: JS16 (Finland)\nGenre: Trance\nLength: 7:26 (original mix), 3:45 (radio edit)\nLabel: 16 Inch (Finland), Neo (UK), Groovilicious (US)\nProducer: JS16, Ville Virtanen\n\n\n“Sandstorm” is an instrumental trance composition by Finnish DJ and producer Darude (Ville Virtanen). It was released as the lead single from his debut studio album, Before the Storm.\n\nInitially released in Finland on 26 October 1999 by 16 Inch Records, the track gained global recognition after being uploaded to MP3.com. It has since become widely known for its usage in sports events and its popularity in internet meme culture. On 1 March 2010, “Sandstorm” was certified Gold in the United States for sales of over 500,000 copies, and in January 2020 it was certified Platinum for sales over one million. The track is noted for its driving beat and distinctive synthesizer melody.",
