    "title": "Nothing Can Come Between Us",
    "description": "Released: June 8, 2007\nRecorded: 2005–2007\nStudio: Not specified\nGenre: Pop, Pop/Rock, Downtempo\nLength: 57:41\nLabel: Soundcolours\nProducer: Piet Blank, Andy Kaufhold, Jaspa Jones (Blank & Jones)\n\nInspired is the comeback studio album by Italian singer and composer Mike Francis, ending a ten-year hiatus from recording. Released on June 8, 2007, the album was produced by acclaimed German electronic duo Blank & Jones, who had convinced Francis to return to the microphone following a cover of Van Morrison's \"Someone Like You\" for their \"Relax\" series. The album consists largely of cover versions of songs that inspired Francis, including interpretations of Seals and Crofts' \"Summer Breeze,\" Sade's \"Nothing Can Come Between Us\" (featuring Amii Stewart), Sister Sledge's \"Thinking of You,\" Culture Club's \"Time,\" and Labi Siffre's \"Down.\" The album also includes original material such as the Italian-language single \"Bossa Per Emilia\" and the closing track \"Friends,\" a new version of the hit Francis originally wrote for Amii Stewart in the 1980s. The album's title reflects Francis's own description of the creative process: \"in a simple and spontaneous way, simply 'inspired'.\n",
