    "description": "Released: 1993\nRecorded: 1992–1993\nGenre: House, Garage House, Deep House\nLength: 5 tracks (EP)\nLabel: Strictly Rhythm\nProducer: Louie Vega, Maurice Joshua\n\nDeep Inside is the debut EP by American house music project Hardrive, the alias of legendary producer Louie Vega, one half of the iconic duo Masters at Work . It was released in 1993 on the seminal New York City label Strictly Rhythm and is widely considered a landmark release of the golden era of house music . The EP was co-produced by Maurice Joshua and engineered by Erick Morillo, featuring sampled vocals from a 1991 interview with an AIDS counselor named Barbara Tucker, who would later become a renowned house diva in her own right . The track has been described as \"the epitome of an evergreen, all-time classic release,\" with its snapping beats, moody bassline, and chopped vocal samples influencing the genre for decades . The EP has been reissued and remastered multiple times over the years, including a 7-inch vinyl pressing, a white vinyl reissue, and a 12-inch remastered reissue in 2018 and 2026",
