    "title": "Call Me",
    "description": "Released: July 29, 1997 (US) / 1997 (Europe)\nRecorded: 1995–1997\nGenre: Eurodance, Euro House\nLength: 52:23\nLabel: RCA Records, Logic Records, BMG\nProducer: Click Production (Andy Brenner, G.A. Saraf)\n\nTonight Is The Night is the debut studio album by the German Eurodance duo Le Click, consisting of Swedish/Nigerian singer Kayo Shekoni and rapper/singer Robert Haynes . The album was created by legendary German producer Frank Farian, who was also responsible for Milli Vanilli and La Bouche . The title track, which first appeared in 1995, featured Melanie Thornton (of La Bouche) on guest vocals and served as Le Click's US chart debut .\n\nThe album peaked at number 49 on the US Billboard Heatseekers chart and number 95 on the German Albums Chart . It produced several successful singles, including \"Call Me,\" which reached number 35 on the Billboard Hot 100, number 4 on the Billboard Hot Dance Club Play chart, and number 38 on the UK Singles Chart . The follow-up single \"Don't Go\" peaked at number 62 on the Billboard Hot 100 .",
