    "description": "Release Date: June 16, 1998 (Canada) \nRecorded: 1997–1998\nGenre: Eurodance, House, Dance-pop \nLength: 1:12:31 \nLabel: ViK. Recordings, BMG Music Canada, RCA \nProducer: Love Inc., Peter Ries, Brad Daymond, Vincent Degiorgio \n\nLove Inc. is the self-titled debut studio album by the Canadian Eurodance group Love Inc., released in 1998 . The group was formed in Toronto, Ontario, by DJ/remixer/producers Chris Sheppard and Brad Daymond, with Simone Denny on vocals .\n\nThe album was a commercial success in Canada, peaking at number 33 on the Canadian Albums Chart and earning Platinum certification from Music Canada . The lead single, \"Broken Bones,\" became the group's first major hit, reaching number 6 on the Canadian Airplay chart and winning Best Video at the 1998 MuchMusic Video Awards . The group performed the song during the halftime show at the 86th Grey Cup . The album's title has sometimes led to confusion with the German techno artist of the same name (Mike Ink) .",
