    "title": "There's a Paradise",
    "description": "Released: May 1995\nRecorded: 1993\nStudio: Not specified in search results\nGenre: Eurodance\nLength: 4:09 (radio mix)\nLabel: EAMS\nProducer: DJ BoBo (René Baumann)\n\n\n“There Is a Party” is a song by Swiss artist DJ BoBo, released in May 1995 as the third single from his second studio album of the same name, There Is a Party (1994). It was written by René Baumann and Axel Breitung, produced by DJ BoBo, and features vocals by American singer Lori Glori (Lori Hölzel). The track became a top‑10 hit in Belgium and a top‑20 hit in Finland, Germany, Lithuania, the Netherlands, and Switzerland, peaking at No. 33 on the Eurochart Hot 100. It also charted in Australia and was certified gold in Germany for selling 250,000 copies. The music video was filmed in Miami, Florida, directed by Frank Paul Husmann‑Labusga. Criticism highlights its reggae‑tinged style, which distinguished it from typical Eurodance productions of the time.",
